  Remmel Dam is also listed on the National Register of Historic Places.\n\n<gallery>\nNPS hot-springs-regional-map.pdf|Regional map over Hot Springs\nLake Catherine State Park 001.jpg|Lake Catherine  \n</gallery>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of Arkansas dams and reservoirs]]\n*[[National Register of Historic Places listings in Garland County, Arkansas]]\n*[[National Register of Historic Places listings in Hot Spring County, Arkansas]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060516142456/http://www.arkansasstateparks.com/parks/park.asp?id=2 Lake Catherine State Park]\n*[http://www.arkansas.com/lakes-rivers/lake/id/11 Lake Catherine]\n*[http://www.arkansas.com/lakes-rivers/lake/id/18 Lake Hamilton]\n\n{{Protected areas of Arkansas}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lake Hamilton And Lake Catherine}}\n[[Category:Reservoirs in Arkansas|Hamilton]]\n[[Category:Protected areas of Garland County, Arkansas]]\n[[Category:Protected areas of Hot Spring County, Arkansas]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Garland County, Arkansas]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Hot Spring County, Arkansas]]\n[[Category:Bodies of water of Garland County, Arkansas]]\n[[Category:Bodies of water of Hot Spring County, Arkansas]]\n[[Category:Dams on the National Register of Historic Places in Arkansas]]\n[[Category:National Register of Historic Places in Hot Spring County, Arkansas]]\n[[Category:National Register of Historic Places in Garland County, Arkansas]]\n", "name_user": "2601:cf:8400:62d0:ed91:15c1:8ed2:80e", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eLake Catherine)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lake_Hamilton_and_Lake_Catherine"}
{"title_page": "Thiruvalla (State Assembly constituency)", "text_new": "{{Infobox Kerala Niyamasabha Constituency\n| constituency number    = 111\n| name                   = Thiruvalla <br/> \u0d24\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d41\u0d35\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32\n| existence              = 1957 - present\n| reserved               = None\n| current mla            = [[Mathew T. Thomas]]\n| party                  = [[Janata Dal (Secular)]] \n| front                  = {{legend2|{{Left Democratic Front (Kerala)/meta/color}}|'''[[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|LDF]]'''|border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n| electedbyyear          = [[2016 Kerala Legislative Assembly election|2016]]\n| district               = [[Pathanamthitta district|Pathanamthitta]]\n| electorate             =   2,08,798 (2016)\n| self governed segments =\n}}\n'''Thiruvalla State assembly constituency''' ({{lang-ml|\u0d24\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d41\u0d35\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32 \u0d28\u0d3f\u0d2f\u0d2e\u0d38\u0d2d\u0d3e \u0d28\u0d3f\u0d2f\u0d4b\u0d1c\u0d15 \u0d2e\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d21\u0d32\u0d02}}) is one of the 140 [[Kerala Legislative Assembly|state legislative assembly]] constituencies at the state [[Kerala]] in southern [[India]]. It is also one of the 7 [[Kerala Legislative Assembly|state legislative assembly]] constituencies included in the [[Pathanamthitta (Lok Sabha constituency)|Pathanamthitta Lok Sabha constituency]].<ref>{{cite web\n |url         = https://pathanamthitta.nic.in/ml/elected-members-and-constituencies\n |website     = pathanamthitta.nic.in\n |title       = State Assembly Constituencies in Pathanamthitta district\n |accessdate  =16 March 2020\n}}</ref> The current MLA is [[Mathew T. Thomas]] of [[Communist Party of India (Marxist)|CPI(M)]]\n==See also==\n* [[Thiruvalla]]\n* [[Pathanamthitta district]]\n* [[List of constituencies of the Kerala Legislative Assembly]]\n* [[2016 Kerala Legislative Assembly election]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Kerala Assembly Constituencies}}\n\n{{Kerala Niyamasabha elections}}\n\n[[Category:State assembly constituencies in Pathanamthitta district]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Kerala Niyamasabha Constituency\n| constituency number    = 111\n| name                   = Thiruvalla <br/> \u0d24\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d41\u0d35\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32\n| existence              = 1957 - present\n| reserved               = None\n| current mla            = [[Mathew T. Thomas]]\n| party                  = [[Janata Dal (Secular)]] \n| front                  = {{legend2|{{Left Democratic Front (Kerala)/meta/color}}|'''[[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|LDF]]'''|border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n| electedbyyear          = [[2016 Kerala Legislative Assembly election|2016]]\n| district               = [[Pathanamthitta district|Pathanamthitta]]\n| electorate             =   2,08,798 (2016)\n| self governed segments =\n}}\n'''Thiruvalla State assembly constituency''' ({{lang-ml|\u0d24\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d41\u0d35\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32 \u0d28\u0d3f\u0d2f\u0d2e\u0d38\u0d2d\u0d3e \u0d28\u0d3f\u0d2f\u0d4b\u0d1c\u0d15 \u0d2e\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d21\u0d32\u0d02}}) is one of the 140 [[Kerala Legislative Assembly|state legislative assembly]] constituencies at the state [[Kerala]] in southern [[India]]. It is also one of the 7 [[Kerala Legislative Assembly|state legislative assembly]] constituencies included in the [[Pathanamthitta (Lok Sabha constituency)|Pathanamthitta Lok Sabha constituency]].<ref>{{cite web\n |url         = https://pathanamthitta.nic.in/ml/elected-members-and-constituencies\n |website     = pathanamthitta.nic.in\n |title       = State Assembly Constituencies in Pathanamthitta district\n |accessdate  =16 March 2020\n}}</ref>\n==See also==\n* [[Thiruvalla]]\n* [[Pathanamthitta district]]\n* [[List of constituencies of the Kerala Legislative Assembly]]\n* [[2016 Kerala Legislative Assembly election]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Kerala Assembly Constituencies}}\n\n{{Kerala Niyamasabha elections}}\n\n[[Category:State assembly constituencies in Pathanamthitta district]]\n", "name_user":