play)|They Knew What They Wanted]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1977\n| [[Drama Desk Awards]]\n| [[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Actor in a Musical|Outstanding Actor in a Musical]]\n| ''[[The Robber Bridegroom (musical)|The Robber Bridegroom]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Tony Awards]]\n| [[Tony Award for Best Actor in a Musical|Best Actor in a Musical]]\n| ''The Robber Bridegroom''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 1978\n| [[New York Film Critics Circle Awards]]\n| [[New York Film Critics Circle Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]]\n| ''[[Movie Movie]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 1979\n| [[National Society of Film Critics Awards]]\n| [[National Society of Film Critics Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]]\n| ''Movie Movie''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 1989\n| [[Golden Globe Awards]]\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Series, Miniseries or Television Film|Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Series, Miniseries or Television Film]]\n| ''[[War and Remembrance (TV miniseries)|War and Remembrance]]''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2013\n| [[Fangoria Chainsaw Awards]]\n| [[Fangoria Chainsaw Awards|Best Supporting Actor]]\n| ''[[Some Guy Who Kills People]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* Evans, David and Scott Michaels. ''Rocky Horror: Concept to Cult''. London: Sanctuary, 2002.\n* Lipton, Michael A. and Nancy Matsumoto. \u201cSerial Dad: Michael J. Fox Looks Up to 6\u20194\u201d Actor\u201d. People March 10, 1997: 99.\n* Uhry, Alfred. \"The Trail of the Robber B\". The Robber Bridegroom CD Liner Notes 1998: 2.\n* Hunt, Paula. \"Bostwick Tells Story of Survival\". Express-News, March 6, 2006.\n\n==External links==\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* {{iobdb name|23289}}\n* {{IMDb name|960}}\n* {{amg name|7552}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for Barry Bostwick\n|list =\n{{GoldenGlobeSupportingActorTV 1970-1989}}\n{{TonyAward MusicalLeadActor 1976-2000}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bostwick, Barry}}\n[[Category:1945 births]