{"title_page": "Yoann Richomme", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Yoann Richomme\n| image              = Yoann Richomme 2019.jpg\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1983|07|12}}\n| birth_place        = [[Frejus]]\n| death_date         = |\n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = French\n| other_names        = \n| website            = {{URL|www.yoannrichomme.fr}} \n| employer           = \n| known_for          = [[Sailing]] [[Yacht Racing]]\n| occupation         =\n}}\n'''Yoann Richomme''' (born 12 July 1983, [[Frejus]]) is a French navigator, sailor and [[yacht]] skipper. He is a double winner of the [[Solitaire du Figaro]] and won the 2018 [[Route du Rhum]] in the Class 40 category.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.sail-world.com/news/223124/Groupe-Apicil-set-for-the-Transat-Jacques-Vabre |title= Damien Seguin and Yoann Richomme aiming to be the first of the Transat Jacques Vabre non-foilers|publisher=Sail World|date=15 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nRichomme studied as a naval architect at [[Solent University|Southampton Solent University]], and was later was involved in the development of the Figaro 3 yacht.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.yachtingworld.com/extraordinary-boats/veedol-yoann-richomme-record-breaking-lift-40-123128 |title=Veedol: On board Yoann Richomme\u2019s record-breaking Lift 40|publisher=Yachting World|date=10 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe is seeking to compete in the 2024 [[Vend\u00e9e Globe]] event.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.vendeeglobe.org/en/news/19547/yoann-richomme-i-just-did-not-want-to-compromise-and-try-and-go-with-a-poorly-put-together-project |title=YOANN RICHOMME: \" I JUST DID NOT WANT TO COMPROMISE AND TRY AND GO WITH A POORLY PUT TOGETHER PROJECT.|publisher=Vendee Globe|date=15 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 February 2020 it was announced that Richomme will skipper the Mirpuri Foundation Racing Team's 'Racing for the Planet' boat in the 2021 running of [[The Ocean Race]]<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.sail-world.com/news/226255/The-Ocean-Race-MFRT-announces-its-skipper |title= Yoann Richomme announced as Skipper for Mirpuri Foundation Racing Team's The Ocean Race campaign |publisher= Sail World|date=4 February 2020}}</ref>  <ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.theoceanrace.com/en/news/12386_Richomme-to-lead-Mirpuri-Foundation-Racing-Team-in-2021-22.html |title= YRichomme to lead Mirpuri Foundation Racing Team in 2021-22 |publisher= The Ocean Race|date= 4 February 2020}}</ref>. As such, Richomme will skipper the Mirpuri Foundation Racing Team's first full team entry in the race, having previously had involvement in the Turn the Tide on Plastic entry in the 2018 race<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.yachtsandyachting.com/news/226255/The-Ocean-Race-MFRT-announces-its-skipper?source=email |title= Yoann Richomme announced as Skipper for Mirpuri Foundation Racing Team's The Ocean Race campaign |publisher= Yachts and Yachting|date= 4 February 2020}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.sailweb.co.uk/2020/02/04/yoann-richomme-to-skipper-mirpuri-foundation-racing/ |title= Yoann Richomme to skipper Mirpuri Foundation Racing |publisher= Sail Web|date= 4 February 2020}}</ref>.\n\n\n== Racing record ==\n\n===Figaro Class===\t\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Competition !! Team !! Finishing Position !! Partner\n|-\n| 2019|| [[Solitaire du Figaro]] || Hellowork - Groupe Telegramme || 1st || Solo\n|-\n| 2016|| [[Solitaire du Figaro]] || [[Macif]] || 1st || Solo\n|-\n| 2016 || Championnat de France de Course au Large Elite || [[Macif]] || 2nd || Solo\n|-\n| 2015 || G\u00e9n\u00e9rali Solo || [[Macif]] || 3rd || Solo\n|-\n| 2015 || Championnat de France de Course au Large Elite || [[Macif]] || 3rd || Solo\n|-\n| 2015 || Tour de Bretagne || [[Macif]] || 3rd || Quentin Delapierre\n|-\n| 2015 || [[Solitaire du Figaro]] || [[Macif]] || 8th || Solo\n|-\n| 2014 || [[Solita